<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1036] change default QParser to eliminate confusion regarding legacy semi-colon sort spec</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1036</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;on the trunk, defType currently defaults to the &quot;lucenePlusSort&quot; option, which has legacy support for syntax like &quot;field:value;sort_field desc&quot; where the semi-colon character is considered special if-and-only-if there is no &quot;sort&quot; param.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this syntax has proved confusing to new users on at least one occasion, and has been deprecated for a while.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 1.4 we should change the default to use defType=lucene and add a note for people upgrading about how to force the legacy semicolon behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
